cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing tasks, specifically abstractive summarization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of large-scale learning and neural text production architectures, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves domain adaptation, which is a topic in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
